          however
        , have they needed charters?

Mr President, the lawful object of the Charter of Rights is to protect the legitimate rights, expectations and aspirations of the citizen against the oppressive behaviour of government, business or other citizens; 
          and
         it is, of course, right that people should be thus safeguarded in respect of the European institutions and their activities.

ParallelChunk.fr:
